# Scientist / Research Assistant SOP

## Code Green

[bold]1.[/bold] While not mandatory, it is highly recommended that Scientists give a prior warning before generating an anomaly, preferably done in-conjuction with the [color=#1b67a5]Research Director[/color] declaring that an anomaly is generated with the Science Communications Console;

[bold]2.[/bold] Scientists are [bold]not[/bold] permitted to carry any weapons generated from the protolathe;

[bold]3.[/bold] Scientists are [bold]not[/bold] permitted to distribute any weapons generated from the protolathe, unless the weapon in question (for example, Proto-Kinetic Accelerators) is delivered to the appropriate department;

[bold]4.[/bold] Scientists are [bold]not[/bold] to activate Station-wide Destruction artifacts, and must destroy or eliminate them as soon as possible;


## Code Blue

[bold]1.[/bold] All guidelines carry over from Code Green;

[bold]2.[/bold] Scientists are permitted to produce weapons and grenades from the protolathe provided they get delivered to [color=#cb0000]Security[/color].

## Code Red

[bold]1.[/bold] All guidelines carry over from Code Blue;

[bold]2.[/bold] In regard to Guideline 2 on Code Blue, scientists may arm themselves with a single weapon if the threat is deemed to be station ending.
